      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suspect you want your various named boolean types to be convertible to each other, but only explicitly?\n\nIf so, maybe try this?\n\n  #define DECLARE_NAMED_BOOL(name)                             \\\n      enum class name : bool { No \u003d false, Yes \u003d true };       \\\n      static bool operator+(name v) { return v \u003d\u003d name::Yes; }\n\nThe last operator+ bit there is optional, but makes it easier to use your named boolean in code:\n\n  void foo(SomeNamedBool option) {\n    if (+option) {\n      ...\n    } else {\n      ...\n    }\n  }\n\nSadly I don\u0027t know a way to define operator bool() for enum classes.  I guess you could write out a longer struct-based version of DECLARE_NAMED_BOOL that could make that work.",
      "revId": "7b28d56accbe51d7c1ca4bf88c8ff3da048a9709",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "18f5360d_761183bf",
        "filename": "include/gpu/GrTypes.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
